narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: James is a great professor. The material isn't super interesting but he helped.

- Strengths: Organized and straightforward
 - Weaknesses: Fast-paced, hard P Sets

Strengths: All course materials were easily accessible, class was extremely well organized, professor was available many times in the week for support 

Weaknesses: Preparation for exams were difficult, as the practice midterms/finals were nothing like the actual assessment. PSets widely varied in work load.
It would be nice to cover problems with the same difficulty as test questions.
Strengths of this course was simple lecture and class structure.

Strengths: Lots of practice problems
Weaknesses: Problem sets and exams were unexpectedly difficult, lack of synthesized, cumulative notes that summarize the course

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes - it is a good QR, and happens to be a requirement for a lot of majors
Yeah! I am not STEM but felt calc 1 was pretty important to have under my belt. Super relevant to many many fields.
Yes, this course was difficult but good at helping improve skills.

If a student needs this course for their major, then yes, they should definitely take it. If they just want a QR that isn't extremely hard, this should work too, especially if they took calculus in high school.
